The paper focuses on the use of the Essence Theory of Software Engineering in an educational setting, which is primarily related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer engineering (cs.CE). The paper also discusses the challenges of bridging the gap between education and industry, which could fall under computer education (cs.ED). The practical project-based course mentioned in the paper could also relate to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG) as students may have used these technologies in their projects.
